nl_problem:
# Task: Multi-Constraint Check (Density 8)
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: isValid(self, n: int) -> bool

# Objective:
Return True if the integer `n` satisfies ALL of the following 8 independent constraints:
1. n is greater than 2
2. n is not equal to 104
3. n is a multiple of 1
4. n is greater than 8
5. n is not equal to 110
6. n is a multiple of 2
7. n is greater than 14
8. n is not equal to 116
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "isValid")
  (signature ( (n int) ) bool)
  (constraints
    (constraint "n must be an integer.")
    (constraint "n must be greater than 2.")
    (constraint "n must not be equal to 104.")
    (constraint "n must be a multiple of 1.")
    (constraint "n must be greater than 8.")
    (constraint "n must not be equal to 110.")
    (constraint "n must be a multiple of 2.")
    (constraint "n must be greater than 14.")
    (constraint "n must not be equal to 116.")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Determine if the input integer `n` satisfies all eight specified constraints.")
    (rule "Check if `n` is greater than 2.")
    (rule "Check if `n` is not equal to 104.")
    (rule "Check if `n` is a multiple of 1 (which is always true).")
    (rule "Check if `n` is greater than 8.")
    (rule "Check if `n` is not equal to 110.")
    (rule "Check if `n` is a multiple of 2.")
    (rule "Check if `n` is greater than 14.")
    (rule "Check if `n` is not equal to 116.")
    (return "Return True if and only if all constraints are satisfied. Otherwise, return False.")
  )
)
